    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so if we're doing CIF, and something goes wrong during transit—like the cargo gets lost or damaged at sea—who is the one actually filing the claim with the insurance provider? is it the buyer or the seller?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you're on CIF, the seller is the one who usually has to deal with the insurance claim, even if the buyer is the one who ultimately suffers the loss. Remember, the seller bought the insurance as part of the CIF deal, so they are the ones who hold the policy. It's a tricky bit, though, because sometimes the paperwork gets tangled up, and you'll need to check the contract very carefully.",
